C++ header: include/emCore/emOwnPtrArray.h
C++ implementation: header-only

C++ public API:
  - template<class OBJ> class emOwnPtrArray
    - emOwnPtrArray()                                                  // construct empty
    - ~emOwnPtrArray()                                                 // delete all owned objects
    - int GetCount() const                                             // element count
    - void SetCount(int count, bool compact=false)                     // resize; new elements NULL, shrink deletes
    - void Compact()                                                   // capacity = count
    - OBJ* const* Get() const                                          // raw C array (const)
    - OBJ** Get()                                                      // raw C array (mutable)
    - OBJ* Get(int index) const                                        // element at index
    - OBJ* operator[](int index) const                                 // element at index
    - void Set(int index, OBJ* obj)                                    // assign at index, delete old
    - void Reset(int index)                                            // Set(index, NULL)
    - OBJ* Release(int index)                                          // release ownership at index
    - void Add(OBJ* obj, bool compact=false)                           // append
    - emOwnPtrArray& operator+=(OBJ* obj)                              // append
    - void Insert(int index, OBJ* obj, bool compact=false)             // insert at position
    - void Remove(int index, int remCount=1, bool compact=false)       // remove range, delete objects
    - void Clear(bool compact=false)                                   // remove all
    - bool IsEmpty() const                                             // count == 0
    - bool Sort(int(*compare)(...), void* context=NULL)                // stable sort
    - int BinarySearchByKey(void* key, int(*cmpObjKey)(...), void*)    // binary search
    - void BinaryInsert(OBJ* obj, int(*compare)(...), void*, bool)     // sorted insert
    - bool BinaryRemoveByKey(void* key, int(*cmpObjKey)(...), void*, bool) // find and remove
    - OBJ* const* begin() const                                        // range-based for (const)
    - OBJ** begin()                                                    // range-based for (mutable)
    - OBJ* const* end() const                                          // range-based for (const)
    - OBJ** end()                                                      // range-based for (mutable)
    - (copy ctor and copy assignment are private/disabled)

  Private:
    - WrappedCmpContext, WrappedCmpObjKeyContext structs
    - void AdaptCapacity(int newCount, bool compact=false)             // realloc strategy
    - static int WrappedCompare(...)                                   // unwrap compare functor
    - static int WrappedCompareObjKey(...)                             // unwrap compare functor

C++ usage in emCore (48 total occurrences across 3 files):
  - emFontCache.h:85: emOwnPtrArray<Entry> EntryArray (member variable)
  - emFpPlugin.h:349: emOwnPtrArray<emFpPlugin> Plugins (member variable)
  - emOwnPtrArray.h: all 42 remaining occurrences are the definition itself

Rust equivalents found:
  - emOwnPtrArray<T> -> Vec<Option<Box<T>>> or Vec<Box<T>> or Vec<T>
    - No direct named equivalent found in Rust codebase
    - emFontCache is not yet ported to use this pattern (uses OnceLock global)
    - emFpPlugin.rs: not found using emOwnPtrArray pattern directly
  - GetCount -> Vec::len()
  - Add/Insert/Remove -> Vec::push(), Vec::insert(), Vec::remove()
  - Sort -> Vec::sort_by() or slice::sort_by()
  - BinarySearchByKey -> slice::binary_search_by()
  - begin/end -> Iterator trait, for-in loops
  - Clear -> Vec::clear()
  - IsEmpty -> Vec::is_empty()

Coverage gaps:
  - emOwnPtrArray's compact/capacity management: no Rust equivalent needed; Vec handles capacity internally
  - BinaryInsert (sorted insert with stable ordering): would use binary_search_by + insert; not found implemented
  - BinaryRemoveByKey: would use binary_search_by + remove; not found implemented
  - The two concrete usages (emFontCache, emFpPlugin) are either not yet ported or use different structures

OPEN QUESTIONS:
  - emFontCache.rs uses a global OnceLock rather than the C++ model/ref pattern; does EntryArray have a Rust equivalent?
  - emFpPlugin.rs exists but its internal Plugins array structure was not verified against emOwnPtrArray<emFpPlugin>

